Package com.lugowoy.helper.filling.array.numbers

Class FillerArrayNumbers<T extends java.lang.Number>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.lugowoy.helper.filling.Filler<Array<T>>
      • com.lugowoy.helper.filling.array.FillerArray<T>
        • com.lugowoy.helper.filling.array.numbers.FillerArrayNumbers<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the numerical data stored and filled into an array.
    public class FillerArrayNumbers<T extends java.lang.Number>
extends FillerArray<T>
    The class is the inheritor of the class FillerArray.

    The class that is a container that encapsulates a specific implementation of a contract declared in the FillingArrayNumbers interface and delegates to it an obligation to perform functionality to fill a array with numeric data.

    This class fills in numeric data objects of class Array, which is a wrapper over classical arrays. It is also possible to fill in numerical data with classical arrays.

    The numeric data must be the inheritance of the base class Number.

    Created by Konstantin Lugowoy on 15-Jan-18.

    Version:
    1.3
    Author:
    Konstantin Lugowoy
